Pakistan Ambassador to China Masood Khalid (right) pins his country's "Hilal-e-Quaid-e-Azam" civil award on Chinese Vice Foreign Minister Kong Xuanyou at the Pakistani Embassy in Beijing on Monday. Photo: Wang Bozun/GTChinese Vice Foreign Minister Kong Xuanyou was conferred Pakistan's civil award "Hilal-e-Quaid-e-Azam" by Pakistani Ambassador to China Masood Khalid on behalf of the country's president at the Pakistani Embassy in Beijing on Monday.At the special investiture ceremony, Khalid presented the award to Kong in recognition of his services to Pakistan and further strengthening of China-Pakistan relations.Kong is serving as Vice Minister of Foreign Affairs, and Special Representative of the Chinese Government on the Korean Peninsular Affairs at the Foreign Ministry. He used to be Assistant Minister of Foreign Affairs from 2015 to 2017, according to the Chinese Foreign Ministry's website."Mr Kong Xuanyou has been a great friend of Pakistan and an ardent advocate of Pakistan-China friendship. Mr Kong has earnestly worked to promote and reinforce all-weather friendship between China and Pakistan. He has cultivated good will for Pakistan in different spheres of influence in China," read a statement from Pakistani Embassy. "In his capacity as Assistant Minister and Vice Minister for Foreign Affairs for Asia, Mr Kong led the Pakistan-China Strategic Dialogue aimed at promoting bilateral relations between the two countries. "Mr Kong and his team have contributed enormously to achieving positive outcomes from regular high-level visits between Pakistan and China, including historic visit of President Xi Jinping to Pakistan in April 2015, and the launch and subsequent consolidation of CPEC," the statement said. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Actress Liu honored with 